main event: A civilian observed an unidentified object in the sky while photographing the moon on October 18, 1967, in Oelwein, Iowa.
interesting points: The observer initially spotted the object while focused on the moon, and later noted that it was about 30 degrees above the horizon,The object moved from a South to Northeast direction and appeared to have lights resembling cabin or landing lights,The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes,The object was described as being the size of the moon through binoculars,There were inquiries made to the observer about the elevation and details of the sighting as part of the investigation.
witness description: civilian who was photographing the moon
